    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. those are good foundational points. one of my students is struggling to go deeper though—they think the 'sovereignty' argument is a bit vague. can you expand on the economic side of that? like, what are the specific arguments regarding labor markets and the strain on public resources that make a strong case for stricter enforcement? try to keep it focused on the most robust, logically sound versions of those arguments without adding the typical counter-arguments for now, since they just need the pro-side build-up first.",
